        "title": "How to split a string by this string: |||",
        "body": "<p>I'm parsing an HTML by jSoup and get the bellow output. the text is splitted by annotators into segments and marked each section by |||. So, I need to retrieve each segment.\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/rtdEq.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">enter image description here<\/a><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>File input = new File(\"C:\\\\Test\\\\aaa.html\");\n                Document doc = Jsoup.parse(input, \"UTF-8\", \"\");\n                Element body = doc.body();\n                String body2 = body.toString();\n                String[] test = body2.split(\"|||\");\n                for (String s:test)\n                System.out.print(s+\"111111111\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>output:\n11111111 111111111&lt;111111111b111111111r111111111>111111111|111111111|111111111|111111111&lt;111111111s111111111t111111111r111111111o111111111n111111111g111111111>111111111 111111111B111111111u111111111s111111111i111111111n111111111e111111111s111111111s111111111 111111111T111111111r111111111a111111111n111111111s111111111f111111111e111111111r111111111s111111111 111111111:111111111 111111111&lt;111111111/111111111s111111111t111111111r111111111o111111111n111111111g111111111>111111111 111111111A111111111s111111111 111111111w111111111e111111111 111111111c111111111o111111111n111111111t111111111i111111111n111111111u111111111e111111111 111111111t111111111o111111111 111111111d111111111e111111111v111111111e111111111l111111111o111111111p111111111 111111111o111111111u111111111r111111111 111111111b111111111u111111111s111111111i111111111n111111111e111111111s111111111s111111111,111111111 111111111w111111111e111111111 111111111m111111111i111111111g111111111h111111111t111111111 111111111s111111111e111111111l111111111l111111111 111111111o111111111r111111111 111111111b111111111u111111111y111111111 111111111a111111111d111111111d111111111i111111111t111111111i111111111o111111111n111111111a111111111l111111111 <\/p>\n",
