            "body": "<p>I am just guessing, but I think you are looking for something like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String s = \"cheese|||bread\";\nString[] splits = s.split(\"\\\\|\\\\|\\\\|\");\nfor (String split : splits) {\n    System.out.println(split);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Output:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>cheese\nbread\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>Implemented in your code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>File input = new File(\"C:\\\\Test\\\\aaa.html\");\nDocument doc = Jsoup.parse(input, \"UTF-8\", \"\");\nElement body = doc.body();\nString body2 = body.toString();\nString[] test = body2.split(\"\\\\|\\\\|\\\\|\");\nfor (String s:test)\n   System.out.print(s+\"111111111\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 60638020,
